( Bot Hunter Analysis Report) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 1. Project context) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter is a review-first bot detection pipeline. It keeps the rules layer readable,) Tj
T*
(lets the anomaly model add statistical coverage, and treats all score outputs as) Tj
T*
(unlabeled operational evidence rather than measured ground truth. That matters because) Tj
T*
(the dataset does not include labels, so precision is reported as an operational) Tj
T*
(confidence estimate instead of a calibrated metric.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 2. Classifiers) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The application implements two classifiers. The first is a rules-based classifier that) Tj
T*
(scores repeated query/domain pairs, repeated queries, high-volume domains, dense) Tj
T*
(region/browser/OS clusters, exact time-to-click reuse, same-second bursts, implausibly) Tj
T*
(fast clicks, and regular pseudo-session inter-arrival timing. Exact time-to-click reuse) Tj
T*
(is selectively calibrated with a 99th-percentile reuse-count cutoff and an absolute) Tj
T*
(floor so the rule can adapt to timer reuse patterns without letting low-count) Tj
T*
(coincidences fire. The second classifier is an Isolation Forest anomaly model over) Tj
T*
(standardized behavioral features. Events that isolate unusually quickly in the fitted) Tj
T*
(forest receive higher anomaly scores.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 3. Methods evaluated but not included) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Bot Hunter also evaluated HDBSCAN, a shallow autoencoder, and a small VAE as optional) Tj
T*
(anomaly backends in prior benchmark work. They were not promoted because they did not) Tj
T*
(improve reviewer utility enough to justify their runtime, memory, or complexity costs.) Tj
T*
(HDBSCAN was much slower than the current anomaly path on the full dataset, while the) Tj
T*
(neural models used more memory and did not produce clearer explanations than Isolation) Tj
T*
(Forest. The production ML path therefore remains Isolation Forest when scikit-learn is) Tj
T*
(available, with k-means as the lightweight fallback.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 4. Anomalies found) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The run analyzed 149,239 events and flagged 3,732 events as bots \(2.50%\). The strongest) Tj
T*
(explainable patterns were:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- repeated query: 3,325 events) Tj
T*
(- repeated query/domain pair: 2,065 events) Tj
T*
(- high-volume clicked domain: 1,902 events) Tj
T*
(- same-second click burst: 1,893 events) Tj
T*
(- very short query: 1,862 events) Tj
T*
